ate=2018-09-26}}</ref> (1785-1853)\n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|'''[[Gynaecology]]'''\n|[[J. Marion Sims]] (1813-1883)\n|{{lower|0.25em|<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sartin|first1=Jeffrey S.|title=J. Marion Sims, the Father of Gynecology: Hero or Villain?|journal=Southern Medical Journal|volume=97|issue=5|year=2004|pages=500\u2013505|doi=10.1097/00007611-200405000-00017|pmid=15180027|url=http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/479892}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.library.wisc.edu/libraries/WomensStudies/bibliogs/hws/hws070401.htm|title=History of Women and Science, Health, and Technology<!-- Bot generated title -->|website=Wisc.edu|access-date=15 January 2018}}</ref>}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|'''[[Histology]]'''\n|[[Marcello Malpighi]] (1628-1694)\n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|'''[[Human anatomy]]''' (modern)\n|[[Vesalius]]<ref>Vallejo-Manzur F et al. (2003) \"The resuscitation greats. Andreas Vesalius, the concept of an artificial airway.\" Resuscitation\" 56:3-7</ref>\n|''[[De humani corporis fabrica]]'' (1543)\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|'''[[Medical genetics]]'''\n|[[Victor McKusick]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ashg.org/pages/mckusick.shtml|title=Page Not Found - ASHG|website=www.ASHG.org|access-date=15 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115124820/http://www.ashg.org/pages/mckusick.shtml|archive-date=15 January 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|''[[Mendelian Inheritance in Man]]'' (started publishing in 1966)\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|'''[[Medicine]]''' (early)\n|{{unbulleted list\n  | [[Imhotep]]<ref>{{cite journal |author=Mostafa Shehata MD |year=2004 |title=The Father of Medicine: A Historical Reconsideration |url= |journal=Turk Klin J Med Ethics |volume=12 |issue= |pages=171\u2013176 [176]}}</ref> (late 27th century BCE)\n  | [[Charaka]]<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Nirupama Laroia M.D. |author2=Sharma Deeksha |year=2006 |title=The Religious and Cultural Bases for Breastfeeding Practices Among the Hindus |url= |journal= Breastfeeding Medicine|volume=1 