eth H. Oakes |page=562 |quote=}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Hermann von Helmholtz]] (1821-1894)\n| {{lower|0.25em|{{big|{{noitalic|'''{{citation needed|date=April 2014}}'''}}}}}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Earth sciences===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n!width=\"25%\"| Field\n!width=\"32%\"| Person/s<br />{{nobold|considered \"father\" or \"mother\"}}\n!width=\"43%\"| Rationale\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| '''[[Geochemistry]]''' (modern)\n| [[Victor Goldschmidt]] (1888-1947)\n| For developing the [[Goldschmidt classification]] of elements.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| Early '''[[geodesy]]''' (mathematical geography)\n| [[Eratosthenes]] (c.276-195/4 BC)<ref>p. 12, ''Plotting the globe: stories of meridians, parallels, and the international date line'', Avraham Ariel and Nora Ariel Berger, Greenwood Publishing Group, 2006, {{ISBN|0-275-98895-3}}.</ref><ref>p. 389, \"Eratosthenes\", D. R. Dicks, in ''Dictionary of Scientific Biography'', ed. Charles Coulston Gillispie, vol. 4, New York: Charles Scribner's Sons, 1971.</ref>\n|Eratosthenes was first to write the word ''Geography'' (from Geo- and -graphy, literally \"writing about the Earth\")\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| Modern '''[[geodesy]]'''\n| [[Al-Biruni]] (973-c.1050)<ref>Ahmed, Akbar S. (1984). \"Al-Beruni: The First Anthropologist\". RAIN. 60 (60): 9\u201310. {{doi|10.2307/3033407}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=iJ0bDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA12&lpg=PA12&dq=al+biruni+father+of+geodesy#v=onepage&q=al+biruni+father+of+geodesy&f=false|title=Interpreting Our World: 100 Discoveries That Revolutionized Geography: 100 Discoveries That Revolutionized Geography|first=Joseph J. Kerski|last=Ph.D|date=17 October 2016|publisher=ABC-CLIO|access-date=15 January 2018|via=Google Books|isbn=9781610699204}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Geology]]''' (modern)\n| {{unbulleted list\n  | [[Nicolas Steno]] (1638-1686)<ref name=\"Woods96\">[[Thomas Woods|Woods, Thomas]]. ''How the Catholic Church Built Western Civilization'', p 4 & 96. (Wa