hovskikh |journal=[[Physics Today]] |volume=58 |issue=11 |pages=70\u201371 |doi=10.1063/1.2155769 |bibcode=2005PhT....58k..70M}}</ref>}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Stratigraphy]]'''\n| [[Nicolas Steno]] (1638-1686)\n| {{lower|0.25em|<ref name=\"Woods96\"/>}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Speleology]]'''\n| [[\u00c9douard-Alfred Martel]] (1859-1938)\n| Began the first systematic exploration of cave systems and promoted speleology as a field separate from geology.\n|}\n\n===Medicine and physiology<!--linked from 'Hippocrates'-->===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n!width=\"25%\"| Field\n!width=\"32%\"| Person/s<br />{{nobold|considered \"father\" or \"mother\"}}\n!width=\"43%\"| Rationale\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Anatomy]]''' (modern)\n| [[Marcello Malpighi]] (1628-1694)\n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n|-\n|rowspan=2|'''[[Biophysics]]''' || [[Henri Dutrochet]] (1776-1847) || |Discovered [[osmosis]]\n|-\n|[[Hermann von Helmholtz]] (1821-1894) || Explained hearing and vision.\n|-\n|'''[[Biomechanics]]'''\n|[[Christian Wilhelm Braune]] (1831-1892)\n|First to describe the methodology of human [[gait]] (walking).\n|-\n|'''[[Bioelectromagnetics]]'''\n|[[Luigi Galvani]]\n|First to discover animal electricity through a series of experiments in 1780.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Cognitive therapy]]'''\n| [[Aaron T. Beck]]\n| {{hlist |\"In developing ways to do this, Beck became the father of cognitive therapy, one of the most important developments in psychotherapy in the last 50 years.\"<ref>{{cite book |last=Durand, V. Mark  |first=Jim |authorlink= |author2=David H Barlow |year=2005 |title=Essentials of Abnormal Psychology |publisher=Thomson Wadsworth |location= |isbn=978-0-495-03128-4 |pages=235}}</ref> |''The Prospect of Immortality'' (1962)}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Cryonics]]'''\n| [[Robert Ettinger]]\n| 1962 book, ''The Prospect of Immortality''{{lower|0.25em|<ref>{{cite web |last=Klein |first=Bruce |title=The Father of Cryonics, Robert C. W. Ettinger, Interview with Bruce Klein |publisher=Immortality Institute   |date=August 13, 2004 |url=http://www.imminst.org/forum/index.php?act=ST&f=67&t=4112 |accessdate=2009-05-24}}</ref>}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Dentistry]]''' (modern)\n| [[Pierre Fauchard]]\n| 1728 book, ''Le Chirurgien Dentiste (\"The Surgeon Dentist\"''), the first complete scientific description of dentistry{{lower|0.25em|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fauchard.org/publications/remembrance.htm |title=The Pierre Fauchard Academy |accessdate=2006-07-22 |last=de Vaux |first=Jean Claude |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20001213092900/http://www.fauchard.org/publications/remembrance.htm |archivedate=2000-12-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>}}\n|-\n|'''[[Electrophysiology]]'''\n|[[Emil du Bois-Reymond]] (1818-1896)\n|The discoverer of nerve action potential.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Emergency medicine]]'''\n| {{unbulleted list\n  | [[Peter Safar]] (1924-2003)<ref>{{cite journal |pmid=17262769 |doi=10.1002/clc.20042 |date=January 2007 |last1=Acierno |first1=LJ |last2=Worrell |title=Peter Safar: father of modern cardiopulmonary resuscitation |volume=30 |issue=1 |pages=52\u20134 |issn=0160-9289 |journal=Clinical Cardiology |first2=LT|pmc=6653261 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|pmid=12759308 |doi=10.1001/jama.289.19.2485 |url=http://www.safar.pitt.edu/content/news/2003/images/Mitka-JAMA%202003.pdf |date=May 2003 |last1=Mitka |first1=Mike |title=Peter J. Safar, MD: 'father of CPR,' innovator, teacher, humanist |volume=289 |issue=19 |pages=2485\u20136 |issn=0098-7484 |journal=JAMA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080627141934/http://www.safar.pitt.edu/content/news/2003/images/Mitka-JAMA%202003.pdf |archivedate=2008-06-27 }}</ref>\n  | [[Frank Pantridge]] (1916-2004)\n }}\n| {{unbulleted list\n  | Safar pioneered [[cardiopulmonary resuscitation|CPR]], [[intensive-care unit]]s and developed standards for [[Emergency medical technician|EMT]], ambulance design and equipment.\n  | Pantridge: {{lower|0.25em|<ref>UK ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'' obituary 12/29/2004.</ref>}}\n }}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Epidemiology]]''' (modern)\n| [[John Snow]]\n| Determining the cause of the [[1854 Broad Street cholera outbreak]] with a combination of public interviews and mapping\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Physical fitness|Fitness]]'''\n| [[Jack LaLanne]] (1914-2011)\n<!--Google Books on \"father of fitness\" turns up Bernarr Macfadden, as I expected, and Joe Weider, but not Jack LaLanne.--dpbsmith-->\n| {{lower|0.25em|<ref>[https://www.today.com/news/father-fitness-jack-la-lanne-turns-90-wbna6123015 Father of fitness, Jack La Lanne, turns 90], MSNBC, September 24, 2004. \"He continues to live by his motto, 'I can't die, it would ruin my image!'\"</ref>}}\n|-\n|'''[[Gastrointestinal physiology]]'''\n|[[William Beaumont]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oculus.nlm.nih.gov/cgi/f/findaid/findaid-idx?c=nlmfindaid;cc=nlmfindaid;view=text;rgn=main;didno=beaumont131|title=William Beaumont Papers|website=oculus.nlm.nih.gov|access-date=2018-09-26}}</ref> (1785-1853)\n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Gynaecology]]'''\n| [[J. Marion Sims]] (1813-1883)\n| {{lower|0.25em|<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sartin|first1=Jeffrey S.|title=J. Marion Sims, the Father of Gynecology: Hero or Villain?|journal=Southern Medical Journal|volume=97|issue=5|year=2004|pages=500\u2013505|doi=10.1097/00007611-200405000-00017|pmid=15180027|url=http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/479892}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.library.wisc.edu/libraries/WomensStudies/bibliogs/hws/hws070401.htm|title=History of Women and Science, Health, and Technology<!-- Bot generated title -->|website=Wisc.edu|access-date=15 January 2018}}</ref>}}\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Histology]]'''\n| [[Marcello Malpighi]] (1628-1694) \n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n\n| '''[[Human anatomy]]''' (modern)\n| [[Vesalius]]<ref>Vallejo-Manzur F et al. (2003) \"The resuscitation greats. Andreas Vesalius, the concept of an artificial airway.\" Re